      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/name": [
      {
        "@value": "Noël choral à la Basilique (Choral Christmas at the Basilica) - Orchestre Métropolitain"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/description": [
      {
        "@value": "<p>This grand choral concert takes audiences on a winter journey blending celebration and enchantment. From the first notes of Humperdinck's <i>Hansel and Gretel</i> to Rimsky-Korsakov's captivating <i>Christmas Eve</i>, the music transports the audience to a magical world. Berlioz, Vaughan Williams and Price add pastoral warmth and comfort with timeless melodies like <i>'Greensleeves.'</i> With Mendelssohn and Rutter, audiences are enveloped in radiant music that celebrates the spirit of Christmas.  </p>\n\n<p><b>Conductor</b> - Léa Moisan-Perrier<br>\nWith the Metropolitan Choir</p>\n\n<p><u>Program</u><br>\n<b>HUMPERDINCK</b> - Hänsel et Gretel : Prélude<br>\n<b>RIMSKI-KORSAKOV</b> - La Nuit de Noël<br>\n<b>VAUGHAN WILLIAMS</b> - Fantasia on Greensleeves<br>\n<b>RUTTER</b> - Gloria<br>\nAnd other choral works from <b>MENDELSSOHN</b>, <b>BERLIOZ</b>, <b>PRICE</b></p>\n\n"
      }
    ],
